This project has two main executables lxc-exec.mjs and webapp.mjs
lxc-exec.mjs -> Simple command line tool to execute tasks (installation, backup) to be used in scripts
webapp.mjs -> As lxc-exec.mjs but with web ui: select application then execute task 

Installation scenario:
Install lxc-manager as lxc container on a ve host.(Currently proxmox only)
Use scenario:
- open the web ui and install lxc containers for the commonly available applications (homeassistant nodered ...)
- create own extended applications and templates with easier setup (e.g. static ip generation...)
The applications:
They have the same purpose:
Make installation of lxc container easy
Make configuration easy by using extended applications and own templates and script in local directory
Allow own applications
Provide templates for easy optional features like disk sharing, usb serial sharing ...
Templates to manage IP Addresses ...
They can be used by creating own extended applications.

